$lang['Hexadecimal is a way of representing binary data in human-readable form. It was developed in the 19th century to allow computers to store large amounts of information.'] = 'Hexadecimal nye mɔ si dzi woato aɖe nyatakaka eve afia le nɔnɔme si amegbetɔ ate ŋu axlẽ me. Woto esia vɛ le ƒe alafa 19 lia me be wòana kɔmpiuta nate ŋu adzra nyatakaka gbogbo aɖewo ɖo.';
$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Àteŋu azã hexadecimal atsɔ atrɔ asi le decimal kple binary ƒe asixɔxɔwo dome. Le kpɔɖeŋu me, ne ètrɔ 10011011001010 wòzu hexadecimal la, ana nàkpɔ 0x4F. Esia fia be asixɔxɔ 4F tsi tre ɖi na xexlẽdzesi eve 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Le akɔntabubu kple kɔmpiutaŋutinunya me la, hexadecimal (si hã nye gɔmeɖoanyi 16, alo hex) nye teƒe ƒe xexlẽdzesiwo ƒe ɖoɖo si ƒe didime, alo gɔmeɖoanyi, nye 16. Ezãa dzesi vovovo wuiade, zi geɖe la, dzesi 0–9 tsɔ tsi tre ɖi na asixɔxɔ zero va ɖo enyi, . kple A, B, C, D, E, F (alo a–f bubu) be woatsɔ atsi tre ɖi na asixɔxɔ ewo va ɖo wuiatɔ̃. Le kpɔɖeŋu me, xexlẽdzesi ade si nye hexadecimal 2AF3 sɔ, le ewolia me, kple (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , alo 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Xexlẽdzesi ade ɖesiaɖe tsi tre ɖi na xexlẽdzesi eve ene (bits) (si woyɔna hã be &quot;nibble&quot;), eye hexadecimal nuŋɔŋlɔ zazã vevitɔe nye abe amegbetɔ xɔlɔ̃wɔwɔtɔe ƒe asixɔxɔ eve siwo woŋlɔ ɖe kɔpi me ƒe nɔnɔmetata le kɔmpiuta kple dijitaal elektrɔnikmɔ̃wo me ene. Le kpɔɖeŋu me, byte ƒe asixɔxɔwo ateŋu atso 0 va ɖo 255 (decimal) gake woateŋu atsɔe afia bɔbɔe wu abe hexadecimal xexlẽdzesi eve le dometsotso 00 vaseɖe FF me. Wozãa hexadecimal hã zi geɖe tsɔ tsia tre ɖi na kɔmpiuta ƒe ŋkuɖodzi adrɛswo.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex nye Hexadecimal ƒe kpukpui, si wotu ɖe gɔmeɖoanyi -16 ƒe wɔwɔme dzi eye wozãnɛ tsɔ naa alesi woɖea mɔfiame siwo wona kɔmpiutawo fianae bɔbɔe. Woto dzesi 16 ƒe xexlẽdzesiwo ƒe ɖoɖo sia vɛ be wòanye mɔnu si dzi woato axe mɔ ɖe xexlẽdzesi eve si ƒe lolome nye bit 8 nu, eyata woate ŋu aŋlɔ nyatakakawo ɖe kɔmpiutawo me agbagbadzedze aɖeke manɔmee. Woate ŋu atae ahaŋlɔe to hex xexlẽdzesi vovovo eve zazã me eye hex xexlẽdzesi ɖesiaɖe aɖe nibble alo ɖewohĩ 4-bits ƒe nɔnɔme afia.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Xexlẽdzesiwo ƒe ɖoɖo sia zãa dzesi 16 siwo woɖe fia le dometsotso si tso 0-9 alo AF me. 0–9 tsi tre ɖi na xexlẽdzesi siwo ade enyi gake AF ya wotsɔ xexlẽdzesi 10–15 tsi tre ɖi na. Ne wotsɔe sɔ kple xexlẽdzesiwo ƒe ɖoɖo ƒomevi etɔ̃ bubuawo la, wobu xexlẽdzesi ade ƒe ɖoɖo be eyae wɔa dɔ wu.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Wò hexadecimal code la mesɔ o';
